{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/head-injury/goals-outcome-measures/audit-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"840e3ede-e526-5282-a63f-af07547e24e4","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 3aa4356c-a99d-4715-9731-6d1b96fa37f2 --><h2>Audit criteria</h2><!-- end field 3aa4356c-a99d-4715-9731-6d1b96fa37f2 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item d84695f6-0788-48c5-ad31-8294cdeb3539 --><!-- begin field 3045208c-a555-4c58-9f7f-a6ae72d34e16 --><p><strong>The following National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) audit criteria are relevant for primary care.</strong></p><ul><li>Patients who have sustained a head injury should be referred to a hospital emergency department, using the ambulance service if deemed necessary, if any of the following are present as a result of the injury:<ul><li>Glasgow Coma Scale (GCS) score of less than 15 on initial assessment.</li><li>Any loss of consciousness.</li><li>Any focal neurological deficit.</li><li>Any suspicion of a skull fracture or penetrating head injury.</li><li>Amnesia for events before or after the injury.</li><li>Persistent headache.</li><li>Any vomiting episodes.</li><li>Any seizure.</li><li>Any previous brain surgery.</li><li>A high-energy head injury.</li><li>Any history of bleeding or clotting disorders.</li><li>Current anticoagulant therapy such as warfarin.</li><li>Current drug or alcohol intoxication.</li><li>There are any safeguarding concerns.</li><li>Continuing concern by the professional about the diagnosis.</li></ul></li><li>Transport patients who have sustained a head injury directly to a hospital that has the resources to further resuscitate them and to investigate and initially manage multiple injuries.</li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/head-injury/references/\">NICE, 2014a</a>]</p><!-- end field 3045208c-a555-4c58-9f7f-a6ae72d34e16 --><!-- end item d84695f6-0788-48c5-ad31-8294cdeb3539 -->","topic":{"id":"9c82c71c-776b-5830-a9b5-f2a1f6e35152","topicId":"22e7906b-f704-4d08-a97c-ab54e669323e","topicName":"Head injury","slug":"head-injury","lastRevised":"Last revised in July 2016","chapters":[{"id":"36484ef0-87eb-5854-8fc9-13ff9e51cd78","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"a7070078-af1b-59a5-a752-8e5e04278465","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"8fdc6898-f17a-5206-ae63-22888799fa23","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"dd05f53c-9e78-5093-955c-34fc3983198b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"18750411-4e80-5f36-987b-228e2d67354c","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"9af40024-874c-5272-93d0-6d40a04c0a49","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"ce894088-4f08-53d3-b4e0-ce8a765c1dd4","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"8dcefa1c-0e26-5c37-ba8b-0e73706e501e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"840e3ede-e526-5282-a63f-af07547e24e4","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"7cab23d8-916a-5694-9eef-78887f368d1f","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"6a9d6f45-556a-5ade-9ff6-d32d2f7a5bb7","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"04a64b49-1bfc-5ccc-b972-367a10a3d60c","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"f354869c-0902-589f-b8a5-eee65f49fee2","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"968fafaf-4ecd-5c8a-907d-584e1fce5a18","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"aaf5f98d-0894-5834-80e7-77201ed31f90","slug":"incidence","fullItemName":"Incidence"},{"id":"376